I'm trying to calculate the price of 15,000 Euro given 15 years ago. I know that the inflation rate in Germany over the past 15 years has been around 2-3%. How can I calculate the equivalent value of 15,000 Euro today?
Comment: You can use the rule of 70 to estimate the effect of inflation on the value of 15,000 Euro over 15 years. The rule of 70 states that the inflation-adjusted value of money is approximately equal to the nominal value multiplied by (1 + inflation rate)^n, where n is the number of years. In this case, (1 + 0.02)^15 = 1.74, so 15,000 Euro today would be equivalent to 26,329 Euro in 15 years.
Answer: \boxed{26,329 Euro}

